        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="cQes9UwB7qMvOyS3TpYK-1" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Handle missing values, duplicates, outliers, inconsistent formats, joins, feature engineering, and encoding so the data is usable for analysis.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="680" x="240" y="278" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="cQes9UwB7qMvOyS3TpYK-6" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;Study distributions, correlations, anomalies, and patterns to understand the problem and shape hypotheses.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="680" x="240" y="368" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="cQes9UwB7qMvOyS3TpYK-8" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;Build a baseline first, then try better algorithms, tune parameters, and compare approaches against the chosen metric.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;You usually start with a simple baseline, then improve by adding better features, more data, or a different method.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="62" width="680" x="240" y="460" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="cQes9UwB7qMvOyS3TpYK-10" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;Test on holdout data or cross-validation, check robustness, and confirm the model actually solves the business problem.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="679" x="241" y="548" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="cQes9UwB7qMvOyS3TpYK-12" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;Put the model into a product, API, batch job, dashboard, or workflow so it creates real value&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="681" x="239" y="640" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="cQes9UwB7qMvOyS3TpYK-14" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;Watch for data drift, performance decay, bias, latency issues, and retraining needs after release.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="680" x="240" y="740" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="cQes9UwB7qMvOyS3TpYK-15" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(39, 37, 30); font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: start; background-color: color(srgb 0.980392 0.972549 0.960784);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;customer churn project &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;refers to rate at which customer discontinuous subscription or in software dev the frequency of changes made to tasks or code. Over all &lt;b&gt;churn &lt;/b&gt;should be minimum.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
